* I've applied PR #3096 (which could affect it?). 
* I am trying to do a deployment without deis-store (see #2812), but, again I don't see how that should affect it.

Deis is deployed to a cluster running at `*.deis-150.somedomain.com`.

We use Route53 for DNS, so the DNS records is an A ALIAS to the ELB. 
I find it hard to believe that this is a DNS issue. It seems more of an application layer issue.

Take a look at this:
```
 server {
        server_name ota.android.pixavi.com;
        server_name_in_redirect off;
        port_in_redirect off;
        listen 80;
}

server {
        server_name ~^android-ota-server\.(?<domain>.+)$;
        include deis.conf;
}
```

Inside `deis.conf` as a result of #3096 there is a `listen 80` on `proxy_protocol`, and `listen 443` on `proxy_protocol`, `ssl` and `spdy`.

