@WilliamHPNielsen A directory for unsupported code is fine I think. I have two remarks:

- Availability of drivers to the core team will change over time (core devs change, hardware will change). We do not want to move drivers between the normal `instrument_drivers` and `unsupported` directories.  (this will break code and confuse people).
- I expected the `qcodes.data.DataSet` to move to unsupported (I do not agree, since there is no proper replacement yet). However, what might be changed in the parameters? There is a lot of code depending on the parameters, so any change has to be done with care.

